    "body": "A bit more context: looks like it's not simply about `HARDHAT_TESTS_SOLC_VERSION`. The whole mechanism for supplying a custom binary seems broken. In cases where the version is one of the released versions, Hardhat tries to use a downloaded binary instead of the one specified in `HARDHAT_TESTS_SOLC_PATH`. And with 0.8.16 it was passing for us only due to cache. After removing cached compiler binaries, tests fail.",
